OL,3,COfficer injured in crash which killed
OL,4,Ccolleague is released from hospital
OL,6,FA police officer from who was injured
OL,7,Fin a crash which killed his colleague
OL,8,Fhas been released from hospital.
OL,10,FPolice Constable Bradley Corke, 27,
OL,11,Fdied after his response vehicle was
OL,12,Finvolved in a collision during an
OL,13,Femergency call out on Thursday 19th
OL,14,FMarch.
OL,16,FThe second officer, who has not been
OL,17,Fnamed, was critically ill in hospital
OL,18,Fafter the incident, but Kent Police
OL,19,Fsay he has now been discharged and
OL,20,Fwill continue his recovery at home.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G1/3
